quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  78,31,"Indeed, the righteous will have salvation"
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,and full-bosomed maidens of equal age
  78,34,"and a full cup [of wine]"
  78,35,They will not hear therein vain talk or lies –
  78,36,a reward and a generous gift from your Lord
  78,37,"[from] the Lord of the heavens and earth and all that is between them, the Most Compassionate; none will dare to speak to Him"
  78,38,"On the Day when the Spirit and the angels will stand in rows; none will dare to speak, except those to whom the Most Compassionate granted permission, and they will only speak the truth"
  78,39,That Day is sure to come. So whoever wills may seek a path leading to his Lord
  78,40,"Indeed, We have warned you of an imminent punishment on the Day when everyone will see what his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever will say, “Oh, I wish that I were dust!”"
  79,1,"By those who pull out [evil souls] harshly"
  79,2,"and by those who draw out [good souls] gently"
  79,3,and by those who glide swiftly
  79,4,and those who overtake one another as in a race
  79,5,"and those who carry out the command [of Allah]"
  79,6,"on the Day when the earth convulses [by the first Blast]"
  79,7,followed by the second Blast
  79,8,hearts will be pounding on that Day
  79,9,and their eyes will be downcast
  79,10,"They say, “Will we be brought back to life"
  79,11,after we have turned into decayed bones?”
  79,12,"They say, “Then that would surely be a losing return!”"
  79,13,It will only be a single Blast
  79,14,then they will immediately be above the ground
  79,15,Has there come to you the story of Moses